 honey","140 g raw sugar"]},{"title":"Orange puddings","content":["70 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces (2 cm), plus extra for greasing","140 g caster sugar","120 g day old bread","200 g almond milk (see Tips)","2 eggs","1 orange, juice and finely grated zest, no white pith","½ tsp ground cinnamon","120 g wholemeal flour","1 tsp bicarbonate of soda","800 g water"]}],"id":"r116825","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-P6BiThdnHDw\/XZWd3pBvUuI\/AAAAAAAAerQ\/FGZa7gRisUAxcFhpeLqvsMSVJ5b3l57HACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Np5d59TpdX4ReFkn.png","title":"Steamed orange puddings with almond milk ice cream","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.1 g","fat":"21.9 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"58.1 g","calories":"1905 kJ \/ 453 kcal"},"usefulItems":"shallow freezeable container, freezable bowl or container, 8 ramekins (125 ml), serving plates, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own almond milk, place 100 g raw almonds and 500 g water into mixing bowl and blend<strong> 1 min\/speed 10. <\/strong>Strain through a nut-milk bag.","Ensure ramekins fit comfortably into Varoma dish so that the lid closes securely and steam can circulate freely.","<strong>Single (large) orange pudding<\/strong>: To make 1 large pudding, grease and coat a pudding basin (20 cm diameter). Ensure it fits into Varoma dish and lid can close securely. Proceed as per recipe, increasing steaming to <strong>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/strong>."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","29h 30m","8 portions"]}